  "ai_prompt_context": "This is a fire-EMS non-transport unit. This unit does NOT transport patients — ALS is co-dispatched and a separate transport unit will transport. Initiate BLS care, stabilize, and prepare for DMIST handoff to ALS. Follow base Michigan protocols for the student's provider level. No agency-specific SOPs or MCA BLS expansions are active. SVN/nebulizer equipment supports scenario-authorized nebulized medications such as albuterol; it does not authorize racepinephrine. Racepinephrine/epinephrine nebulized for croup is a Paramedic/ALS agent-selection item, not a BLS/EMT scope expansion."
